        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 3:00PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 300 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Genesee, or 15 miles northeast of Quincy, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Genesee.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
